  "prompt": "Which is the real photo of Shivaji Maharaj drawn byMir Muhammad?",
  "response": "The real photo of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj drawn by Mir Muhammad is a historical painting, not a photograph, as photography was not available during Shivaji Maharaj's time (1630\u20131680). Mir Muhammad was a court painter in the Mughal Empire, and his depiction of Shivaji is one of the few visual representations from that era. \n\nThis artwork is often cited when discussing Shivaji's appearance, but it should be noted that artistic interpretations can vary significantly and may not represent an accurate likeness. The painting captures the essence of Shivaji as a warrior king, showcasing his attire and facial features according to the style of that period. \n\nIf you're looking for the specific painting, you can find it in historical texts, art collections, or online resources related to Indian history.",
